news.title: Gurugram: ED attaches Rs 68.59 crore assets in Vatika Limited fraud case
news.para: ED investigation revealed that the Company M/s. Vatika Limited is allegedly involved in alluring the investors to make payments for future projects, against high-value returns like assured returns till completion and lease-rent returns after completion of projects.

news.title: Prime minister to distribute 65 lakh SVAMITVA property cards on January 18
news.para: SVAMITVA, a scheme of the Ministry of Panchayati Raj, provides a 'Record of Rights' to village household owners with the issuance of legal ownership cards to the property owners by mapping land parcels using drone technology, it said.

news.title: Sambhal: Demolition notice served to 123 houses in dilapidated state
news.para: Subsequently, the municipality has issued a notice to the owners of all houses and shops and asked to demolish the structures, otherwise the municipality itself will demolish.

news.title: Rajasthan government forms cabinet sub-panel to review merger of ULBs
news.para: Members include cabinet minister for water resources, Suresh Singh Rawat, forest minister Sanjay Sharma, and cooperatives minister Gautam Kumar.

news.title: Creation of separate civic body for Dharwad likely to take time
news.para: The residents of Dharwad who were demanding a separate municipal corporation for the city for the last two decades citing discrimination in taking up development works are elated over the cabinet decision and expect the new DMC to be functional soon.

news.title: Lucknow development body to collect maintenance charges from allottees of vacant plots
news.para: Around 29 petitions were submitted during the day, while seven cases were resolved on the spot, and deadlines were set for addressing the remaining issues.

news.title: UK's Taylor Wimpey warns of rising costs but expects higher homebuilding in 2025
news.para: Excluding joint ventures, Taylor Wimpey built 9,972 homes in Britain in 2024, down about 4%, while total group completions including joint ventures dropped 2.4% to 10,593 units.

news.title: New home prices in China stabilize in December 2024
news.para: That stood in contrast to a 0.1% decrease in November, as calculated by Reuters based on data from China's National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Dahod administration issues notices to 58 property owners occupying govt land
news.para: The matter came to light after it was revealed that the properties were constructed on government land. Property owners presented documents claiming ownership, but the district administration found no such records in their files.

news.title: Nagpur civic body issues 628 warrants to property tax defaulters
news.para: Out of the total warrants, 404 were executed, and 21 were settled on the spot, with Rs20.73 lakh collected from the defaulters. The NMC also attached properties worth Rs 2.66 crore of the defaulters.

news.title: Goa: GIDC expects strong interest in e-auction of industrial plots
news.para: GIDC officials expect the pharmaceutical sector and the logistics industry to show keen interest in the 20 industrial plots at Verna that are being auctioned.

news.title: Privilon Buildcon's directors arrested for Rs 54 crore real estate fraud in Ghuma
news.para: The Ahmedabad Rural police had arrested Hiren Kariya and Jaydeep Kotak, directors of Privilon Buildcon Group, in Dec for duping 240 buyers out of Rs 54 crore

news.title: Himachal Pradesh govt launches land pooling policy in Baddi-Barotiwala
news.para: Under this policy, the BBNDA will take the lead in development projects across residential, commercial, institutional, mixed-use and infrastructure sectors in urbanisable areas covered under approved development plans.

news.title: Indore development body eyes 1000 crore revenue from sale of 31 properties
news.para: According to IDA CEO RP Ahirwar, a total of 31 properties at seven locations have been put on sale through bidding, with a total value of Rs 978 crore.

news.title: Nagpur launches drone monitoring to combat illegal sand mining
news.para: Highlighting the benefits of drone technology, Bidari emphasised that drones equipped with advanced cameras and sensors can provide real-time footage of extraction sites.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC denies bail to builder in Doon land fraud case
news.para: Following complaints from the victims, the state government launched an investigation, later transferring the case to the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI). The CBI investigation implicated Windlass and three associates in the alleged scam.

news.title: YEIDA urges Aligarh administration to halt land registries
news.para: As the registrations are being done under residential category, it could be difficult for the Authority to evict the plot owners, which could jeopardise the multi-modal logistics park scheme, officials said.

news.title: Banks plan to approach SC over lending against properties hurdle
news.para: A ruling by the apex court last month has barred lenders from giving loans where properties kept as collateral do not have completion and occupancy certificates (CCs and OCs).

news.title: Residents of Madh-Marve and Malvani halt land survey for Dharavi redevelopment project
news.para: This is the second time that the collector's office tried to do the survey. A previous attempt before assembly polls was also foiled by locals who are determined not to allow relocation of Dharavi residents to Madh.

news.title: Emaar Properties in talks with Indian groups to sell stake in local business
news.para: The statement followed media reports on Wednesday stating that Adani Realty, the real estate unit of Indian billionaire Gautam Adani's Adani Enterprise, was in advanced talks to acquire a majority stake in Emaar India.
